<item>
            <title>[CLI-349] DefaultParser.parse() throws NullPointerException when options parameter is null</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CLI-349</link>
                <project id="12310463" key="CLI">Commons CLI</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The DefaultParser.parse() method throws a NullPointerException when the options parameter is null.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Steps to reproduce:&lt;br/&gt;
1. Create a DefaultParser instance&lt;br/&gt;
2. Call parse() with null options parameter: Eg.:&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
defaultParser0.parse((Options) &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;, stringArray0, getBooleanJazzer());&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;3. NPE is thrown at line DefaultParser.java:708: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
expectedOpts = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; ArrayList&amp;lt;&amp;gt;(options.getRequiredOptions());&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Expected behavior: The method should validate input parameters and throw a meaningful IllegalArgumentException with a descriptive message.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
