                            <comment id="18010655" author="garydgregory" created="Tue, 29 Jul 2025 12:34:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hello &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=leofernandesmo&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;leofernandesmo&quot;&gt;leofernandesmo&lt;/a&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thank you for your report.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you use a recent version of Java, you get:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;java.lang.NullPointerException: Cannot invoke &quot;org.apache.commons.cli.Options.getRequiredOptions()&quot; because &quot;options&quot; is null
	at org.apache.commons.cli.DefaultParser.parse(DefaultParser.java:747)
        ...
 &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Which is the most precise exception and message you&apos;ll receive from Java.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Nevertheless, we can make this a touch better using Java&apos;s&#160;&lt;tt&gt;Objects.requireNonNull()&lt;/tt&gt; to fail faster with a message specific to the argument. The exception is still an NPE, the most precise for this case.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Done in git master and snapshot builds in &lt;a href=&quot;https://repository.apache.org/content/repositories/snapshots/commons-cli/commons-cli/1.10.0-SNAPSHOT/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://repository.apache.org/content/repositories/snapshots/commons-cli/commons-cli/1.10.0-SNAPSHOT/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
